ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528139\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 19, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104hca1665702857400.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hca1665702857400.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hca1665702857400.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"hca1665702857400\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      File-Naming Considerations on Microsoft Windows\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"hca1665702857400__file_naming_considerations_on_microsoft_windows_59236\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hca1665702857400__p_d17537e1_d17538e1_d17539e1\">Microsoft Windows uses the following naming conventions:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hca1665702857400__li_d8150e1_d8151e1_d8152e1\">File: {<var class=\"keyword varname\">DriveMapping</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">:</code>}{<var class=\"keyword varname\">Directory</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">/</code>}<var class=\"keyword varname\">FileName</var>{<code class=\"ph codeph\">.</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Extension</var>}\n <p class=\"p\" id=\"hca1665702857400__p_d17540e1_d17541e1_d17542e1\">For example <span class=\"ph filepath\">d:/uniface/readme.txt</span>.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hca1665702857400__li_d8153e1_d8154e1_d8155e1\">Directory: {<var class=\"keyword varname\">DriveMapping</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">:</code>}<var class=\"keyword varname\">Directory</var>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hca1665702857400__p_d17543e1_d17544e1_d17545e1\">For example <span class=\"ph filepath\">d:/uniface</span> or <span class=\"ph filepath\">d:/uniface/</span>.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hca1665702857400__li_d8156e1_d8157e1_d8158e1\">Universal Naming Convention (UNC): <code class=\"ph codeph\">//</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">ServerName</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">/</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">NetName</var> or <code class=\"ph codeph\">//</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">ComputerName</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">/</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">ShareName</var>.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hca1665702857400__p_d17546e1_d17547e1_d17548e1\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">DriveMapping</var>:</code> prefix is not acceptable as Uniface generic syntax. They are passed 'as is' to the operating system.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hca1665702857400__p_d17549e1_d17550e1_d17551e1\">In path and file names, all special characters, including both Windows allowed characters (embedded periods, spaces, and so on) and Windows disallowed characters (colon, asterisk, vertical bar, and so on) are passed 'as is' to the OS. Uniface does not check the syntax of any such path name or file name.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hca1665702857400__p_d17552e1_d17553e1_d17554e1\">To keep your file names and directory names as generic as possible when you use file management ProcScript, use Uniface logicals in your assignment file to prefix the names with a Windows-specific drive mapping. See <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xat1719648016613.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xat1719648016613.html\" title=\"To write ProcScript that is independent of the underlying operating system, follow these guidelines when specifying files and directories.\">Guidelines for Writing Platform-Independent ProcScript</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gxx1719646855788.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Syntax of File and Directory Names</a><p>You can choose to specify file and directory names generically or using platform-specific names—the ProcScript statements and functions for local file system management accept both.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528139\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528139\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "File-Naming Considerations on Microsoft Windows Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 19, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 File-Naming Considerations on Microsoft Windows Microsoft Windows uses the following naming conventions: File: { DriveMapping : }{ Directory / } FileName { . Extension } For example d:/uniface/readme.txt . Directory: { DriveMapping : } Directory For example d:/uniface or d:/uniface/ . Universal Naming Convention (UNC): // ServerName / NetName or // ComputerName / ShareName . The DriveMapping : prefix is not acceptable as Uniface generic syntax. They are passed 'as is' to the operating system. In path and file names, all special characters, including both Windows allowed characters (embedded periods, spaces, and so on) and Windows disallowed characters (colon, asterisk, vertical bar, and so on) are passed 'as is' to the OS. Uniface does not check the syntax of any such path name or file name. To keep your file names and directory names as generic as possible when you use file management ProcScript, use Uniface logicals in your assignment file to prefix the names with a Windows-specific drive mapping. See Guidelines for Writing Platform-Independent ProcScript . Related Links Syntax of File and Directory Names You can choose to specify file and directory names generically or using platform-specific names—the ProcScript statements and functions for local file system management accept both. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}